        "description": "If one puts a field that is one of the partitioning variables in {{group_by()}} and then summarises, we get a segfault:\r\n\r\n{code:r}\r\nlibrary(arrow)\r\nlibrary(dplyr)\r\n\r\ntemp <- tempfile()\r\n\r\nwrite_dataset(mtcars, path = temp, partitioning = \"cyl\")\r\n\r\nds <- open_dataset(temp)\r\n\r\n# this works just fine\r\nds %>% \r\n  group_by(gear) %>% \r\n  summarise(\r\n    sum(mpg)\r\n  ) %>% \r\n  collect()\r\n\r\n# however this segfaults (regardless of the aggregation, even simply n()) \r\n#  *** caught segfault ***\r\n# address 0x0, cause 'memory not mapped'\r\nds %>% \r\n  group_by(cyl) %>% \r\n  summarise(\r\n    sum(mpg)\r\n  ) %>% \r\n  collect()\r\n{code}",
